# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback — paths without a matching static file return
# the home shell with HTTP 200 so React Router can resolve them on the client.
# Prerendered routes (`/`, `/sobre`, `/cards/<id>`, etc.) match real files and
# are served directly; this rule only fires for state-driven SPA routes like
# /results, /compare, and unknown URLs. Note: catch-all `/*` rewrites override
# static file matches in Cloudflare Pages — see the path-aware client logic in
# src/main.tsx that decides hydrate vs createRoot based on window.location.
# Reference: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
/*  /index.html  200
